This spontaneous report received from a patient concerned a 73-year-old white and non-Hispanic or Latino female. The patient's height, and weight were not reported. The patient's concurrent conditions included: asthma. The patient received covid-19 vaccine (dose number in series 1) (suspension for injection, route of admin not reported, batch number: 043A21A and expiry: 19-SEP-2021) dose was not reported, 1 total, administered on 07-APR-2021 to left arm for prophylactic vaccination. Concomitant medications included chewable airborne. Ascorbicacid/herbalnos/levoglutamide/lysine/magnesium/manganese/retinol/riboflavin/selenium/tocopherol/zinc).  On an unspecified date, laboratory data included: Blood pressure 105/60 millimetres of mercury. On 07-APR-2021, the patient did not feel well within minutes after vaccination. The patient asked a nurse to check her after the 15-minute wait. The emergency medical technician checked blood pressure of patient and it was elevated to 190/80 millimetres of mercury. The emergency medical technician checked blood pressure of patient again, after about 15 minutes and it was 180/70 millimetres of mercury at 17:20. When patient was walking to her car to leave her nostrils closed, lips itched, eyeballs felt funny. The patient was still trying to get home with her special needs child. The patient did not feel it effect lungs. The feeling wore off in approximately five hours. Blood pressure of patient was 137/68 millimetres of mercury at 23:00 that night. Next morning (08-DEC-2021) patient felt wobbly, shaky and felt like she was coming down with something. The patient lost her zip lock bag with all the cards and could not find it in the car, so she drove back to the vaccination site to try and find the bag with the cards. Did not find them there. Patient then drove home, and, in the morning, patient called the vaccination site gymnasium to try and locate the cards. The patient found the cards at the vaccination site. The patient recovered from blood pressure increased, nostrils closed, lips itched, eyeballs felt funny, shaky, wobbly, felt like coming down with something, and did not feel well on 09-APR-2021. This report was serious (Other Medically Important Condition).; Sender's Comments: V0: 20211260647-COVID-19 VACCINE blood pressure increased. This event(s) is considered unassessable. The patients son called to report a serious side effect that his mother experienced following Moderna second dose. In April-2021, developed a dry cough/hack and then started to developed pain in left side of her back. The caller took her to hospital, and they ran a bunch of tests, then the discharged her to follow-up with her doctor. On a Friday, for the follow up appointment when she came out of the office she could barely walk, she holding to the rail. When she got into to car she doubled over into his lap because she could not breathe, and had trouble speaking. She could only get a couple words at time before heaving for air. She continued laboring to breathe and declined going to the hospital citing chronic sinus issues. On the following Sunday morning she called him and asked to be taken to the hospital, she was doubled over from the waist down and he had to call an ambulance to take her to Hospital. She was admitted 1 day and 1 night. The physicians suspected blood clots but did not have the equipment for tests. They transferred other hospital 4-5 days. She was hooked up to every dang machine in there, and had a lot attention. She did not have the energy to eat. The physicians again suspected that she had blood clots all over her body. She went into some sort of epileptic seizure, it was like she was in short circuit and getting electrocuted. She continued having these violent fits where she tried to rip everything off. On 15-Jul-2021, doctors were trying to perform a dialysis for a kidney issue she had, she was sedated for this procedure. She passed away at 9:30 PM that night. The nurse informed that she went through one of those fits, and her heart could not take.  Following these events, a retired nurse at hospital contacted the reporter specifically stated that large group left after this and the mandates and they firmly think this was caused by the Moderna vaccine. A multicenter cohort of patients with liver injury following COVID19 vaccination was reported, cohort includes 16 total patients aged25 to 74, who presented between 5 to 46 days following their first vaccine dose (Pfizer 12, Moderna 4). Notably 75% of patients presented after their second vaccine dose. Six patients had a history of chronic liver disease including 4 with autoimmune hepatitis in treated remission. The majority of cases demonstrated a hepatocellular pattern of liver injury (peak alanine aminotransferase: 96 to >5,000 U/L). Of the remaining 3 cases, 1 was cholestatic and 2  were mixed. Acute liver injury (ALI, defined as international normalized ratio >1.5) occurred in 3 patients; no patients developed acute liver failure. Treatment details were not disclosed in the abstract. The benefit-risk relationship of mRNA-1273 vaccine is not affected by this report. Extreme fatigue, headache, shivering/chills, night sweats, and muscle aches/soreness especially back and legs. Some joint pain in hips and ankles.  These started the next morning after vaccination. The next day I had several nightmares. And started to have a stabbing pain that I could feel in my chest and the same location in my back (like someone stabbing me from my back through to my chest)
Within minutes of vaccination, itching of cheeks and chin; then fullness in throat and sensation of difficulty swallowing.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I am not sure exactly when I started getting the side effect but it was not immediately after the booster. I would say 7-10 days after the booster. The date I noted is approximate.  I am getting an itch all over my body but mostly on my back and legs. Even my scalp, fingers, toes and bottom of my feet too. It itches more if I wear tight clothes. For example, when I wear a bra I get an intense itch and redness where the elastic touches my skin. When I scratch my skin becomes very red and welts. I can clearly see where I scratched. I think the condition is called Dermatographia. I've never experienced this before.  An urgent care center prescribed me hydrocortisone cream to spot treat the itch. I am not using because calamine lotion helps. They also advised that I take Aleve during the day and Benadryl at night. I've been doing this for the past 3 days and it prevents the itch most of the day. When the meds wear out the itch comes back with the same intensity. It has not improved since it began.
OTHER_MEDS: Birth control Jaimiess, probiotics, multivitamin , vitamin D + K2

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Woke up with the feeling of my heart fluttering or beating fast and felt slightly out of breath.  Had to focus on relaxing and taking deeper breaths to alleviate it.  Found it difficult to sleep that night.  I had never experience this feeling before.    Several times since then, I have felt the same sensation and it seems to coincide with higher stress at work, but I've never had this sensation before I had the vaccine from stress or otherwise.
5 minutes following vaccine administration, developed itchy throat, which of 2 hour duration. Resolved without treatment.
Had typical sore arm, tired, and shivers. However between the first and second vaccine and after the second vaccine I have on and off rapid heartbeat/palpitations

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Started out as a rash on my left torso in early July. Over time it started spreading and I started getting hives. The hives seemed to "travel". They would go away from one spot and then pop up in another. Zyrtec helped some but not completely. The itching seemed to "change shifts". For awhile it would be worse in the morning � other times in the evening. There were several periods where I could not sleep more than 2 to 4 hours without waking up because of the itching. In October and  November the hives began "weeping". It was as if some sort of toxic glue was oozing out of my pores and it was at times painful, especially after getting out of the shower. By the end of November it seemed to have evolved into eczema. Dry itching flaky skin all over my body. I went to Urgent Care on November 27 because the pain and the itching were unbearable. I was prescribed Oral steroids � Antibiotics � and prescription Antihistamines. They fast tracked me an appointment with the dermatologist he he prescribed topical steroids. Since the beginning of December I have been taking Hydroxizine 1 every six hours. Zyrtec 1 every 12 hours. On around Dec 10 I started taking a "mega -dose" of vitamin D3 5000IU one every 12 hours. The healing seemed to accelerate after I started the D3 and it seemed like my histamine levels also continued to lower. ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- SUMMARY THAT I SENT TO ALLERGIST Symptoms: Symptoms began on approximately July 12 2021. Scaly patch on left and right torso and on shoulders. In a short time progressed and spread with hives on legs and behind the knee. Wound on left leg from scratching in my sleep.  I had already had problems with itching on that leg due to venous stasis dermatitis.  Water and sweat make affected areas itchy red and swollen. On most nights I can only sleep 2 to 4 hours at a time before waking up with itch. Sometimes the affected areas have a burning sensation. On a few other rare occasions the patches on my torso felt as if they tickled. There is nothing consistent about the intensity,frequency, and location of the symptoms. They vary from day to day and hour to hour. I must make note that the patches on my torso disappeared after the first 3 weeks and then returned about 1 week ago.  Triggers: Water � Sweat  Sleep The condition is sometimes (not always) triggered by pressure from sitting or lying down.  Treatment: 1 H1 (Alternate Zyrtec and Allegra every other week) + 1 H2 (Tagamet)  2X per day (every 12 hrs.) Tylenol � for occasional pain flares in wound on leg. Relieve itches by applying hair dryer to affected area. Elevate legs against the wall with pillows behind back. Walking to increase  blood flow and distract from itching.   Supplements: 2 Adult Multivitamin 2 D3 1 B3 1 Zinc 1 E  � tsp. C crystals dissolved in 100% Cranberry juice 3 drops nascent iodine + 1 Selenium B12 supplement 1 to 2 times weekly  Herbals: 1 Ginkgo Biloba 2 Echinacea/Goldenseal 1 eyedropper of Echinacea tincture Ginseng supplement  1 to 2 times weekly NOTE: I have been drinking Green Tea w/lemon juice (NO SUGAR) nearly every day for approximately the last 4 years. I use several brands but I have not changed them or the source from where I buy them.    Have had bad reaction to:  Benadryl ( both Oral and topical) VERY bad reaction to Zzzquil. I am allergic to it. Hydocortizone  -  Swelling on leg after scratching which led to cellulitis. Calamine Lotion � intense itching � had to rinse off immediately. Cetaphil - intense itching � had to rinse off immediately. Aloe Vera Gel - intense burning � had to rinse off immediately. Coconut Oil � was very irritating. Neosporin greatly irritated leg wound. NOTE: During the first few weeks I tried several "home remedies" by washing up with water and a very small amount of   *Tea Tree Oil   - minimal to zero effext  *Apple Cider Vinegar burns if not diluted properly. *Bleach  initially cleared up patches on torso but is too dangerous for any areas of broken skin. *Baking Soda (initially soothes but does not last) *Gold Bond Lotion � initially soothes but wears off fairly quickly. Comments: *Sometimes hair dryer brings relief for as long as 12 hours. Other times it does not help at all. *Hair dryer works more often than it doesn't. *Hair dryer satisfies the urge to scratch and  feels as though I am actually scratching *Sometimes taking NyQuil allows me  to sleep as long a 8 hours. Other times I wake up itching 2hours after taking it. * Prednisone helped only on the 1st day I took it. After that there was not much difference. * Hydroxyzine  helped only on the 1st day I took it. After that there was not much difference. * I do not like the way Prednisone and Hydroyzine affected me mentally and physically. *Gabapentin literally makes me intoxicated. On day two I woke up itching 2 hours after taking it. *Tested my well water with a kit that checks 13 conditions. PH reads 9 to 10. Alkalinity 240ppm. All others good,. *I cleaned and flushed both the water softener and water heater. Hardness level was dramatically    improved,however my symptoms are still aggravated when my skin gets wet. PH still at 9. Alkalinity reduced to 180ppm.  Reliability of home water test is questionable. We no longer have white powdery residue on topsoil of houseplants.    * I stopped drinking the tap water about two weeks into this however there was never any effect either way. *THERE HAVE BEEN NO  CHANGES IN MY DIET, ENVIRONMENT, OR THE CLEANING PRODUCTS THAT I USE OR THE CLOTHES THAT I WEAR. It is still however possible that the manufacturers may have added ingredients. It is also possible the airborne allergens may have been introduced into my environment.  * We have no pets in  our household nor do I have frequent encounters with animals. * We have numerous houseplants that we have had for 10+ years. We have not purchased any new plants in the past year. *Aside from intermittent clutter on desks and tables, our house is clean. My wife regularly sweeps ,mops ,vacuums and dusts. *We run an air purifier most of the time to help my wife with her allergies (filter changed routinely) *I do yard work � mowing and weeding � weekly and sometimes daily. I usually bathe and change clothes immediately afterward. * Aside from my symptoms and lack of sleep there have been no other excessive stressors in my life. *NOTE: On two occasions last year (2020) , I had a minor unexplained rash on both wrists that lasted for about 3 weeks. Both of these incidents seemed to coincide with a peak of Covid cases in the local region as reported in the news. I had no other Covid symptoms and I never got tested. During both periods there were a few employees at work who had tested positive and had to quarantine. --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------    It was in mid December that I discovered perhaps a dozen threads on a web forum discussing similar experiences after receiving the covid vaccine. Threads that were posted on the forum discussing skin disorders that were similar to mine. Most of these occurred after receiving a Moderna or Pfizer vaccine. Although there is no actual proof that the MRNA vaccines are the root cause of these disorders, there seems to be too many people with a similar experience to just simply ignore this. It is not my intention to make negative and aggressive accusations, but to make the medical community aware of  this problem and to hopefully prevent other people from going through months of extreme discomfort as I have.  As a side note I must also mention that these posts cannot be found using the usual search engine. I found them using a different search engine.   Below are Doctor's notes from my appointments. Progress Notes 10/29/2021  3:30 PM History of Present Illness: See both today's allergy questionnaire and dictation for complete HPI elements including location, quality, severity, duration, timing, context, modifying factors and associated signs and symptoms. Allergy questionnaire also compliments PFSH.      The patient is a 58-year-old who I am seeing at the request of Dr. for my opinion on his urticaria.  According to the patient, since July he has had urticaria on a pretty much daily basis.  There have been a few days and he has done better and he has tried everything under the sun to help him with his symptoms.  High-dose antihistamines, namely both 4 a day of Allegra and Zyrtec, did not help.  Prednisone did not help, at least more than a day, and he has tried all sorts of lotions and creams and avoiding things.  What seems to work the best for him is if he heats up in a hot shower or a hair dryer, I think he de-granulates his mast cells and then they do not release the histamine again for 6-8 hours, but that is certainly not a quick fix.  He has had a lot of allergy testing and food testing.  He has definitely a lot of positive ImmunoCAPs, but he has done elimination diet and that has not revealed any results either, that no specific food is causing any problems, at least at this time.  He has had a normal CBC and chemistry profile and he does not have any other symptoms.   Review of Systems:  Including constitutional, eyes, ears, nose, throat, neck, respiratory, cardiovascular and GI are all negative except as noted.   Physical Examination:  Revealed a well-developed, well-nourished 58-year-old in no acute distress.   Impression/Plan:  My impression is that patient has chronic idiopathic urticaria, unresponsive to high-dose antihistamines and unresponsive to prednisone, and at this point we will prior authorize him for Zyrtec since he has failed these prior treatments.  He is not committed to doing the Xolair.  He has read a lot about it and is reluctant to start it, but I said we will prior authorize him and at least offer it to him, and we can take it from there.  He will call with any questions or problems and he will call me if he would like to proceed. Clinical Data: Pruritic dermatitis x 30 days DIAGNOSIS: PUNCH BIOPSY, R flank: SUBTLE LOW GRADE SPONGIOTIC DERMATITIS (SEE NOTE) Specimen Site: R flank Gross Description: Specimen received in formalin, vial labeled with patient's name, 5x3x4 mm skin wedge. Punch, tan, not oriented. 1 piece tissue received, 2 portions submitted in 1 block. All tissue submitted. Microscopic Description:  Original and multiple deeper sections contain a punch biopsy of skin with a very sparse superficial perivascular inflammatory-cell infiltrate. There is very minimal spongiosis. There is focal and minimal parakeratosis as well. The inflammation is lymphohistiocytic in nature. Diagnosis: SUBTLE LOW GRADE SPONGIOTIC DERMATITIS (SEE NOTE) Note: The changes are extremely subtle and are not unequivocally diagnostic. There is very minimal spongiosis and on balance, given the clinical impression, I slightly favor a low grade spongiotic dermatitis such as contact, nummular, or atopic dermatitis. Nevertheless, these changes are quite subtle in zones and therefore entities such as asteatotic dermatitis could conceivably produce such findings as well. Clinical correlation is required.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I full on started a menstrual cycle I believe a few days after injection. I went through all of the normal side effects including vomiting, and went into work three days after said injection. Shortly after, I started spotting, and now I appear to be having my full on period even though I am on birth control. I have also felt very tired, and I ended up sleeping all day today 12/30/2021. I also believe I was constipated for a period of 3-4 days which is unusual for me having a history of Crohn's. I have had a ton of prolonged bowel movements over the past two days. As of tonight, I have now developed the strangest sensation of enhanced hearing of low frequencies. I believe it is only in my right ear, but here is the following description I gave my mother: "idk what is going on, but tonight I have been hearing like, bass sounds over-amplified in my ear? like, walking sounds from upstairs and sometimes vehicles and the music from the bar across the st are abnormally loud. I can hear normal sounds fine enough though? maybe slightly muffled.... my ears do feel "full" though if I focus on it. hopefully it's gone tomorrow but it's fairly jarring to hear sounds that you should not normally be able to hear well heard OVER normal sounds. it's like I have super hearing for sounds no wants wants to hear lol. it would be cool if it was in normal hearing range, like voices, but instead it's like BOOM. someone took a single step nearby." I do not know if this is vax related, but I figured it should be included as it is something that happened shortly after with the constipation and odd super early period. I am hoping it will be gone tomorrow, but I have included it as an adverse event that is currently affecting me as I worry it may be some sort of swelling.
OTHER_MEDS: calcium supplement, magnesium supplement, multi mineral supplement, spironolactone 75 mg, 0.15 mg of levonorgestrel and 0.03 mg ethinyl estradiol

First day after injection soreness, light swelling and redness of injection site. By the second day swelling and redness had spread. Tenderness of site was more pronounced followed with itchy skin. By the third day the injection site redness and swelling had started to spread around the top part of the arm starting to go under armpit area still having tenderness and itching of skin. By the fourth day the swelling and redness had increased to the point the arm was extremely tender and felt hard.  I saw  fit to go to urgent care at this point to be on the precautionary side due to the extreme discomfort and limited mobility due to swelling. Doctor informed me I was having a reaction to the vaccination I received and suggested that I do not get the second dose because the reaction could be more severe.  I was prescribed a steroid to take. After roughly a week the swelling had went down significantly and the itching was not as prominent  however there is now a bruise like discoloration of the skin at the injection site.
LAB_DATA: None

The occurrence of additional non-serious events is detailed below.     Concurrent medical conditions included Seizures (Patient had minor seizures twice a month).   On 02-Oct-2021, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (unknown route) 1 dosage form. On 05-Dec-2021, received second dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (unknown route) dosage was changed to 1 dosage form. On 05-Dec-2021, the patient experienced INTENTIONAL PRODUCT USE ISSUE (First dose  more than 25 days before second dose). In December 2021, the patient experienced SEIZURE (Seizures) (seriousness criterion medically significant), VACCINATION COMPLICATION (Had more seizures and side effects from the vaccine/her body went into side effects) and FATIGUE (She was tired and out of it). On an unknown date, the patient experienced CONDITION AGGRAVATED (Condition aggravated). The patient was treated with CANNABIS ongoing since an unknown date for Seizure, at an unspecified dose and frequency. On 05-Dec-2021, INTENTIONAL PRODUCT USE ISSUE (First dose  more than 25 days before second dose) had resolved. At the time of the report, SEIZURE (Seizures) and CONDITION AGGRAVATED (Condition aggravated) outcome was unknown and VACCINATION COMPLICATION (Had more seizures and side effects from the vaccine/her body went into side effects) and FATIGUE (She was tired and out of it) was resolving.            No concomitant medication was reported. She got the second shot, and then got a seizure. Then in the late afternoon, her body went into [hard to describe] side effects, which were still there. She had to go lay down. It was really scary because she never had it. Last night. 14-Dec-2021, she had a seizure. She was tired and out of it. On top of that, she also had the other side effects that she had in the afternoon. She was worried that what if she has this for the rest of her life. It was a scary feeling if not sure if it will ever go away. On 15-Dec-2021, she was feeling better. She started taking cannabis for the seizures about 2 months ago. She will up the dosage on the cannabis. She states she waited for the second one because she was having a seizure once a week, which never happened to her. Company comment: This case concerns a 65-year-old, female patient with medical history of seizures (she had minor seizures twice a month), who experienced the unexpected serious AESI of seizure and non-serious event Condition aggravated. One episode of seizures occurred 9 days after the second dose of mRNA-1273 vaccine but is it not clear when the event onset was or if she had other episodes. The rechallenge was positive, since she referred that she had seizures after the first dose for 5 weeks and that seizures reappeared after the second dose, although she also referred using cannabis which could be a potential confounder. The mentioned medical history remains as a confounder. Intentional deviation from dosage regimen was reported by the patient. The benefit-risk relationship of mRNA-1273 vaccine is not affected by this report. Case was assessed as serious due to important medical event and medical judgement. The following information was reported: MYALGIA (non-serious), ARTHRALGIA (non-serious) all with onset 2021, outcome "unknown" and all described as "but then his muscles and joints begin to hurt again"; PAIN IN EXTREMITY (non-serious) with onset 2021, outcome "not recovered", described as "Legs hurt little bit when walked a lot"; MUSCLE TWITCHING (non-serious) with onset 2021, outcome "unknown", described as "Developing twitching in muscle in his legs all the way down to his feet"; INSOMNIA (non-serious) with onset 2021, outcome "unknown", described as "Would sleep for 5 hours if he was lucky"; TINNITUS (non-serious) with onset 2021, outcome "recovered" (2021), described as "tinnitus started in his ears"; NEURALGIA (non-serious) with onset 2021, outcome "unknown", described as "nerves are picking up the foreign objects and sending pain signals"; GAIT INABILITY (non-serious), outcome "unknown", described as "could not walk"; INFLAMMATION (non-serious), outcome "unknown", described as "inflammation". The events "but then his muscles and joints begin to hurt again", "legs hurt little bit when walked a lot", "developing twitching in muscle in his legs all the way down to his feet", "would sleep for 5 hours if he was lucky", "tinnitus started in his ears", "but then his muscles and joints begin to hurt again", "nerves are picking up the foreign objects and sending pain signals", "could not walk" and "inflammation" were evaluated at the physician office visit. Therapeutic measures were taken as a result of myalgia, pain in extremity, muscle twitching, insomnia, tinnitus, arthralgia, neuralgia, gait inability, inflammation. Additional information: Things were pretty good. Legs hurt little bit when walked a lot, which didn't exist before  Went in and the nurse was concerned about it. Stated he needed to have some protection from this thing. 3 days later, pain again in legs started. Pain didn't feel like legs were being beat or hit with something, but they ached inside. He was toughing it through Taking Advil and Tylenol and all kinds of stuff trying to keep pain under control. Would sleep for 5 hours if he was lucky. States then maybe it will start to wear off, the immune system response is wearing off. Figured if it's not going away, it's getting worse. From what he was reading, in 10 weeks. the immunity to COVID is built up. Thought when the immunity stops building up, maybe the pain will stop then, but it didn't. Started developing twitching in muscle in his legs all the way down to his feet. Almost feels like he had shingles once when he was in his twenties from chicken pox or wherever it comes from. When he goes to walk quite a bit, it feels like the pain is getting the muscle like when had shingles. He talked to a doctor, a neurologist who is retiring and explained what was going on. Neurologist stated what's happening is the antigen from the virus is lodged in muscles in his legs. The nerves are picking up the foreign objects and sending pain signals that something is wrong. Was advised to take Gabapentin 100mg at night and 100mg in morning because it needs to turn the pain off so the sensory nerves will die. This has been going on. Gabapentin does help, but makes him a little groggy. Taking Advil because he believes there's inflammation there. Taking fish oil to relive inflammation. Taking Vitamin C. Caller was speaking to his pharmacist about what the neurologist advised him to do. Pharmacist said eventually it should go and hopefully caller will build sensory nerves back without pain. States it's really strange. He's talked to so many people. Heard many different reactions people have. Nobody is having anything like he is having. Caller was a pro athlete. Never had any particular injuries. Would like to get rid of this problem. He had his 2nd shot on 28Jul2021, he was feeling good, his legs are working okay, he hasn't been able to use his legs a lot because they hurt too much to use for 10 days. After getting the 2nd dose, he didn't feel any reaction for 3 days, but then his muscles and joints begin to hurt again, mainly the hip joints, tinnitus started in his ears, that went on. He's on his 15th week of pain in his legs and it had been getting worse and at around 12 weeks, his muscles and legs began to twitch. Per caller, the Primary Care doctor doesn't have any idea on what medication he should be taking. He's taking Tylenol and Advil, he's also taking Gabapentin for 2weeks. Caller also added that he spoke to his Pharmacist who's giving out Pfizer-BioNTech. He had been having muscle pain now from his hips now to his feet for 17 weeks. He had a lot of leg pain going on from the vaccine. He was desperate after 17 weeks of pain. The provider who was trying to contact us is a neurologist who has him on Gabapentin 100mg, up to 4 a day. A couple of weeks ago his muscles were hurting so bad, that it was incapacitating him and could not walk, and the leg muscles from his hip to his feet were twitching. Most of the twitching has dissipated, but if he walked around too much they start to ache more. He was cutting branches outside before this. He take one of our products Advil, he took 1 to 3 a day, and it helps a lot. Tylenol does not touch it. He took 200mg of Gabapentin today and will take another 100mg at 11:30 at night when he went to bed. His own doctor who has been his doctor for 25 years. He took fish oil, he spoke to an advisor, and he recommended fish oil which he was up to 7000mg a day now, and turmeric is very good antioxidant for inflammation. The doctor was looking for medications that may be given to people with muscle pain, because he says about 14 to 15 percent of people have this problem, but maybe not as long as him. It was reported that patient received his shot, nine days later. Large red egg on his upper right arm. That stayed for another 9 days and was still there, just not red. Hurts all the time. His body ached and his heart starting beating fast. He had taken digoxin for 30 years. He knew about fast beating hearts. Knew that an ingredient in his shot monopotassium phosphate may increase the hyperkalmic activity of digoxin. No one asked if he took a heart pill at the Pfizer blitz at his local clinic. He was not a scientist and off course they will say he misunderstood what he read. Did not matter. They did not test digoxin and the interaction. How many died. They call it underlying heart issues. Or his favorite age. He asked to don't call him elderly like they did at the start of this form. It is disgusting. that tells he that they don't care about anything but making money. What is 1percentage of 5000. Should that many have a reaction or die. Just wondering. Patient did not had covid prior vaccination nor tested for covid post vaccination. Patient had known allergies. Additional information: After reading their letter and looking at their questionnaire he had a couple of questions. Are you really asking me for all of my medical and my family medical information? Why? I want more information than you telling me that you want information. Isn't that private information. I will tell you it was in my left arm not my right where I received the shot. I did visit with a couple of people about your request and will be visiting with one more when they are available. Prior Vaccinations (within 4 weeks) were none. Patient was not sure what he should say. On 10Mar he went to the Pfizer Blitz the local clinic. it was fine. Nothing happened until 9 days later when he come out of his morning shower and looked in the mirror and saw a red oval shaped swelling on his left arm above his small pox shot and going up to the top of his arm. He did send an email to the clinic and someone wrote back to put a ice pack on it. He had sent them a picture even. The ice pack didn't work. He had paroxysmal SVT and he took digoxin for it. He had this for most of his life. He know about his heart. The next day it was racing and the digoxin was not working. No one at the vaccination clinic asked if he had a heart condition. Their whole purpose was to get a needle into his arm. It was like a picture of the army lining up recruits to give them every shot they could. He wasn't impressed. It wasn't just his heart that acted up, there were odd things like the side of his mouth was numb at times. His arms, hands and legs ached and burned. Them were odd things that happened like for about 3-4 months his hair curled like he had a perm put in it. Everyone would comment how nice his perm was. It was so thick and curly. He kept cutting it and now in Dec it is back to what it was. He still have curls but not like what he had. He spent a lot of time on the internet studying the ingredients of your vaccine. No one on digoxin should take your vaccine. (i know i am not a great scientist but when it says that digoxin can interact with monopotassium phosphate and you list monobasic potassium phosphate, he really begin to wonder and yet no one mentions it. Even if i am a 1% of the population, it is too many. if you have 5000 people and 1% die of a reaction or even have some reaction, it is too many. Get out of your sterile labs and see people, not statistics. He went for his annual physical (yes i go every year) and my digoxin levels were down and his blood pressure was up. So I was put on a beta blocker as well as the digoxin. He finally went off of the digoxin because heart acted like it had the hiccups. So for now, he was on a beta blocker, his arm still hurts and he can see a faint outline of the egg shaped whatever it is. He had bacterial pneumonia in Apr2020 and spent 4 days in the hospital. It started with a viral sinus infection but he couldn't get well. Everyone thought he had covid. He didn't. But, as a result of the pneumonia, his potassium level went below three and he spent a few hours in outpatient on potassium ivs. It hurt. He had nothing more to say. He had a letter from his doctor not to have anymore vaccine. He stay away from people. He work from home. He still wear a mask. He was more afraid of vaccinated people than he was of unvaccinated people. Vaccinated people think they are entitled to do what they want. They have convinced people that vaccines are the way to go. Penicillin was thought of that way also and they found people became immune to it. Will that happen with vaccines, also.  Follow-up attempts are completed. No further information is expected.

high blood pressure/blood pressure went to 220 after the Pfizer and it stayed 193, 185; it stayed for months/blood pressure went over the roof; This is a spontaneous report received from contactable reporter (consumer) from Medical Information team. The reporter is the patient.  A 70 year-old female patient received BNT162B2 (PFIZER-BIONTECH COVID-19 VACCINE, Solution for injection), administered in arm left, administration date 27Feb2021 around midday (Lot number: EN6203, Expiration Date: Jun2021) at the age of 70 years as dose 1, single for COVID-19 immunization. The vaccine was not administered at facility. The patient had no relevant medical history. There were no concomitant medications. The patient had no prior vaccinations (within 4 weeks). The patient had no family medical history relevant to the adverse event (AE). The following information was reported: HYPERTENSION (medically significant) with onset 10Mar2021, outcome "unknown," described as "high blood pressure/blood pressure went to 220 after the Pfizer and it stayed 193, 185; it stayed for months/blood pressure went over the roof." The event was evaluated at the physician office visit. The patient underwent the following laboratory tests and procedures: blood pressure: (10Mar2021) 220, 193, and 185, notes: high; (2021) 179 and 175, notes: doctor prescribed Losartan and the blood pressure was still high like 179, 175; (2021) 150, 160, and 140, notes: during the day, blood pressure was much lower it was like 150, 160, 140; (2021) 180 and 195, notes: at night if she woke up, it still could be 180, 195; blood tests: (2021) normal; colonoscopy: (10Mar2021) unknown; echocardiogram: (2021) unknown; electrocardiogram (EKG): (2021) normal; urine tests: (2021) normal. Therapeutic measures were taken as a result of hypertension, which included losartan and hydrochlorothiazide (HCTZ). The patient relayed that since having the two primary doses, she had experienced high blood pressure since Mar2021. She did not have high blood pressure prior to receiving the vaccine. She stated that the nurse should have taken her blood pressure before the shot and after to see if it went up. She had seen a cardiologist and had an EKG and an echocardiogram done. She had been placed on high blood pressure medications and 'water pills.' She stated her blood pressure would go up to 220, 198, and 183. She had read a study that the vaccine causes high blood pressure. She relayed that the doctors didn't know and that they deny the high blood pressure was related to the vaccine, but that she was sure it is. She would like Pfizer to know that this was a side effect. The patient expressed concern that she currently had to take medications to treat her blood pressure, but that they would have negative effects on her kidneys and liver over time. She stated that she did not feel bad or have any physical symptoms of the high blood pressure. The patient was asking what ingredient was causing the high blood pressure. She stated that myocarditis and pericarditis were known side effects with the vaccine and wanted to know how she would know if she had inflammation in the heart. It was relayed to the patient that elevated blood pressure was not a side effect that was reported during clinical trials and because of this, there was no data for it and was referred to speak with healthcare professional (HCP) if she was concerned for this condition or had further questions. The patient did not know if she should receive the booster dose of the vaccine or if it would just make her blood pressure higher and her doctors did not know. The patient was asking if she could have the Moderna booster dose instead. The patient was again referred to speak with HCP regarding fruther questions. It was further reported that she was due to get the booster and she had concerns, but nobody could answer her questions. She suffered from side effects, clarified that ''her blood pressure went over the roof after she had the first and second dose of the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine. Her blood pressure went up to 220. They did not check her blood pressure during the COVID-19 vaccination, but she had an appointment for a colonoscopy on 10Mar2021, wherein they woke her up and was shaking her like she was so angry, she was told her blood pressure was 220 and then 193 and then 185. They called all the doctors and made such a big fuss and did an EKG. Her blood pressure was high at night, but she took medication in the morning during the day so its lower during the day. All the time she went through all the tests, she was asking herself why she had high blood pressure; she thought it was connected to the colonoscopy, since this was the first time she knew about her blood pressure being elevated. She knew and read research that a lot of patients that took the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine had blood pressure increased. She was asking what ingredient in the vaccine could be causing the blood pressure increase. She was a 100% healthy person before the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine. She read it causes myocarditis and was asking if the booster would make her blood pressure worse. The patient reported that for 5 months, she refused to take medication, she thought maybe the side effects would disappear if it was from the vaccine and she was drinking beets and celery to lower the blood pressure. She wanted to know why she had the blood pressure increased, so she went to the cardiologist and had tests. Even during the colonoscopy, the doctors rejected it, clarified the doctor stated that her increased blood pressure had nothing to do with vaccine. When she asked her primary doctor if she should take the booster, she was told according to CDC the benefit outweighed the danger. The blood pressure went through the roof was discovered during the colonoscopy on 10Mar2021. The patient further reported that she was looking online for the booster. She had two Pfizer shots. First one on 27Feb2021 and the second one on 20Mar2021 and she had terrible side effects. The doctors were saying it's not possible. The patient was trying to get the tests from the doctor's what was causing the high blood pressure and they didn't know. The EKG was normal, the blood tests were normal, the urine tests were normal, and they were saying they didn't know, but she should take medication for the high blood pressure, but she refused the medication, because she was a senior citizen and was in excellent health. The patient didn't have any problems till of the Pfizer her blood pressure went over the roof and she started to be very concerned and so she didn't take any high blood pressure medication, because she didn't want more side effects, but her blood pressure stayed in April, in May, in June, in July. Then her doctor told her that she could drop dead anytime from high blood pressure and she had to start the medication. So, she started the medication like two or three months prior reporting. The doctor prescribed losartan and the blood pressure was still high like 179, 175. So, they told her that she should take a water pill, so, that's a long name for that medication. She didn't remember the name, but it's a water pill. So she was taking those two medications and they increased losartan to two pills, so she was taking 1 in the morning, 1 in the evening, and in the middle of the day, she was taking the water pills. So, during the day, her blood pressure was much lower, it was like 150, 160, 140, but at night if she woke up, since she didn't take medication, it still could be 180, 195. The (withheld), they did research and they found the side effects of Pfizer, the heart inflammation, the muscles or in the chamber or on the outside. So, she had this concern because, she spoke to the doctor about the booster. She was afraid to take Pfizer booster, because it might increase to the problem with her heart and they said, CDC, they commented that the benefits outweighed the side effects. So, the patient didn't know if she should take the Pfizer booster and she was worried, because there were restrictions for people who didn't take the booster that like if she wanted to travel if she didn't show that she had the booster, maybe they would decline her travel. So, she wanted to report that because she didn't make it up, it had really happened to her and she was sure it happened to other people and she visited the cardiologist, who didn't know what was causing the high blood pressure. The patient wanted Pfizer to give her answers if she should take the booster, because she didn't want to have heart problems, didn't want to be paralyzed or have a heart attack.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I?m a retired physician in generally good health for 85 years. In March 2020 I had a mild case of Covid-19 with no late after effects and in February 2021 twice received mRNA Covid vaccines (Pfizer) without incident. A routine health exam on October 13, 2021 included basic laboratory tests, all of which were normal except for elevated glucose, and I was given a Flu shot. The very next day I had a Covid-19 booster at a local pharmacy ? then things got complicated.  On October 15, 2021 I attended an outdoor event and stood for nearly two hours in 80 degree heat. Feeling faint, I lay down and drank water and that night was surprised to note gross hematuria. I had no history of kidney disorders and only the next day was there moderate left flank pain. A CT urogram revealed a radiolucent 7 mm stone obstructing the mid left ureter. I was hospitalized and when a urologist inserted a ureteral stent to decompress the kidney, the stone was pushed back up into the renal pelvis. Three weeks later ureteroscopy and lithotripsy was performed, the stent then was reinserted for three more weeks. (Follow-up CT urogram performed on 1/3/22?..)   Almost unnoticed amidst all this, a rash had developed behind my left eyebrow, soon followed by small lesions on the temple, forehead and nose. Then there was unilateral neck and scalp tenderness that initially I attributed to cervical arthritis ? until I awoke on December 4 with slightly blurred vision and noted conjunctivitis of the left eye. I realized that the rash corresponded with the dermatome of the ophthalmic division of the trigeminal nerve and only then did I understand that Herpes Zoster (HZ) from long forgotten childhood chickenpox must have become activated. An ophthalmologist confirmed presence of acute iritis and increased intraocular pressure and I was begun on eye drops, including tapering doses of a steroid.. I?d never received a shingles vaccination and it was decided not to begin an antiviral because by now, it probably was several weeks since initial eruption of the rash and scalp tenderness ? too late for benefit. Pain was managed with nonprescription analgesics.
Red raised hot air, with severe pain

The reporter is the patient.  A 70 year-old female patient received bnt162b2 (BNT162B2), administered in arm left, administration date 20Mar2021 in midday (Lot number: EN6205) at the age of 70 years as dose 2, single for covid-19 immunisation. The patient had no relevant medical history. There were no concomitant medications. Vaccination history included: Bnt162b2 (Dose:1, Time: Around midday, Anatomical location: left arm, Lot: EN6203, Expiration: Jun2021), administration date: 27Feb2021, when the patient was 70 years old, for Covid-19 immunization, reaction(s): "high blood pressure/She states her blood pressure will go up to 220, 198, 183/I was in excellent health; I didn't had any problems till of the Pfizer my blood pressure went over the roof". The following information was reported: HYPERTENSION (medically significant) with onset Apr2021, outcome "unknown", described as "blood pressure stayed in Apr, in May, in Jun, in Jul"; EYE HAEMORRHAGE (medically significant) with onset 2021, outcome "unknown", described as "she had bloody eye, completely bloody/blood vessel that broke"; PERIPHERAL SWELLING (non-serious) with onset 2021, outcome "unknown", described as "her feet were swollen"; JOINT SWELLING (non-serious) with onset 2021, outcome "unknown", described as "she could not see her ankles". The event "blood pressure stayed in apr, in may, in jun, in jul" was evaluated at the physician office visit. The events "she had bloody eye, completely bloody/blood vessel that broke", "her feet were swollen" and "she could not see her ankles" were evaluated at the emergency room visit. Clinical course as follows: She is currently 71 years old. She wanted to tell about the side effects of Pfizer covid 19 vaccine. Now she is due to get the booster and she has concerns and nobody can answer her questions. She suffered from side effects, clarified that her blood pressure went over the roof after she had the first and second dose of the Pfizer covid 19 vaccine. Her blood pressure went up to 220. They did not check her blood pressure during the covid vaccination but she had an appointment for a colonoscopy on 10Mar2021. They woke her up and was shaking her like she was so angry, she was told her blood pressure was 220 and then 193 and then 185. They called all the doctors and made such a big fuss and did an EKG. All the time she went through all the tests, she was asking herself why she has high blood pressure, she thought it was connected to the colonoscopy since this is the first time she knew about her blood pressure being elevated. She knows and read research from France that a lot of patients that took the Pfizer covid 19 vaccine had blood pressure increase. She is asking what ingredient in the vaccine could be causing the blood pressure increase. Asks should she take the booster. She was a 100% healthy person before the Pfizer covid vaccine. She read it causes myocarditis. Asking if the booster will make her blood pressure worse. Reports that for 5 months she refused to take medication, she thought maybe the side effects would disappear if it was from the vaccine and she was drinking beets and celery to lower the blood pressure. She wanted to know why she had the blood pressure increase so she went to the cardiologist and had tests. Even during the colonoscopy the doctors rejected it, clarifies the doctor states that her increased blood pressure had nothing to do with vaccine. When she asked her primary doctor if she should take the booster, she was told according to cdc the benefit outweighs the danger. She had 3 strange episodes, one day she woke up and she had bloody eye, completely bloody and she called doctor and she was asking the nurse what it could be. She thought maybe her brain is bleeding. She went to ER but she was not admitted. She saw the doctor and looked in her eye and said it is just a blood vessel that broke and nothing needs to be done. One day she woke up and she noticed that her feet were swollen and this has never happened before her in life. She was so surprised she could not see her ankles. This happened one to three months ago. patient stated, "I was looking online for the booster. I had two Pfizer shots. First one 27Feb2021 and the second one, 20Mar the same year (2021) and I had terrible side effects. You know the doctors were saying no it was not possible. My blood pressure went to 220 after the Pfizer and it stayed 193, 185 its stayed for months and I was trying to get the tests from the doctors what was causing the high blood pressure and they were saying we did not know. The EKG were normal, the blood tests were normal, the urine tests were normal and they were saying we did not know but you should take medication for the high blood pressure and I refused the medication because I am a senior citizen, age 71 (Further not clarified) and I was in excellent health. I did not had any problems till of the Pfizer my blood pressure went over the roof and I started to be very concerned and so I did not take any high blood pressure medication because I did not want more side effects but you know my blood pressure stayed in Apr, in May, in Jun, in Jul. Then my doctor told me that I can drop dead anytime from high blood pressure and I have to start the medication. So, I started the medication like two or three months ago. The doctor prescribed Losartan and the blood pressure was still high like 179, 175. So, they told me that I should take a water pill, so, thats a long name for that medication. I did not remember its a water pill. So I am taking those two medication and they increase Losartan to two pills so I take 1 in the morning 1 in the evening and in the middle of the day I take the water pills. So, during the day my blood pressure is much lower it is like 150, 160, 140 but at night if I wake up since I did not take medication it still can be 180, 195. So, I want to report this to you because I found online information from France. The French they did research and they found the side effects of Pfizer the heart inflammation, the muscles or in the chamber or on the outside. So, I have this concern because I spoke to the doctor about the booster. I am afraid to take Pfizer booster because it may increase to the problem with my heart and they said, CDC, they comments that the benefits outweigh the side effects. So, I did not know if I should take the Pfizer booster and I am worried because you know there are restrictions for people who did not take the booster that like if I want to travel if I did not show that I had the booster maybe they will decline my travel. So, I wanted to report that because I did not make it up its really happened to me and I am sure it happened to other people and I visited cardiologist and he did not know what is causing the high blood pressure. What is the reason? What is the ingredient in the Pfizer that effect the heart? Because you see now when I was reading about side effects it says myocarditis, inflammation of heart muscles. Pericarditis, inflammation of the lining outside heart. So, is the booster going to bad for me. I want the Pfizer to give me answers. Should I take the booster? Because I am 71 and I did not want to have heart problems. I did not want to be paralyzed or have a heart attack. So, can you give me the answer?" As happened with my 2nd Moderna vaccine, I developed hives a little over a week after the shot. Last time it was on my torso and feet with intense itching usually around 7-8 pm (I thought that the timing thing was really strange). This time around it manifested on my head, forearms, buttocks and, now, clavicle area. The itching was even more intense and then came the swelling of my head. I woke on the second day of this with swelling around my head, from the temple area, behind the ears and around the back of my head. It felt like the reaction I get to a bee sting, like a thick pad of something forming beneath my skin. I had taken a Benadryl before bed, then a Zyrtec in the morning to keep the itching at bay (with varying results). I iced the swollen area and the swelling subsided after an hour, but the temple are remained swollen. The swelling was moving too close to my eye for comfort, so I went to the local clinic to be examined. I was prescribed a steroid, which seems to have helped. The only itching and hives are now around my neck/clavicle area.
LAB_DATA: None.
PRIOR_VAX: 02/03/21 Moderna 010M20A (Mall Site), age 56, Itching/hives - torso and feet, no swelling lasting more than 1 week, but bearable

Four days after my Moderna COVID booster shot, I began to experience symptoms similar to POTS.  The problem started on November 27 with nausea, bloating, fatigue and lightheadedness after yardwork that involved a lot of stooping and standing back up.  On December 11, I ended up in the emergency room and Hospital. when my resting blood pressure was 170/120 due to severe nausea   Blood testing and an EKG did not show issues with my heart.  I had a follow-up appointment with Dr. on December 13.  I had an ultrasound to check my gall bladder, but it was clear.  I started Cipro on December 17 which helped with bloating and some with the nausea.  The POTS symptoms continued to grow worse with time.  By December 26, my heart rate when standing was 140 compared to 65 lying down.  Simple tasks like goig to the bathroom resulted in severe dizziness and nausea.  I lost 15 pounds in one month.  Since this time, the POTS symptoms have improved.  Today, my heart rate when standing is 105 compared to 65 when lying down.  I've gained a couple of pounds back.  I have not driven an automobile since December 10th.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I had no difficulties with the first two Moderna vaccines given in April and May of 2021 - minor myalgia for which I didn't need any medication.  However with this booster dose, I had a severe response that evening with very bad myalgia, shaking chills, with some nausea and headache.  The reaction was so severe that I could not sleep, and could barely get around. Finally at 1:00 AM I took a Tylenol with only minimal relief.  In the morning, I still felt like I had been "hit by a truck", to the point of tears because I had work to do.  I took one more Tylenol at noon, trying to minimize analgesics.   This was quite unexpected, as I had no anxiety about getting the booster shot, and on-line information reports that the reaction to the Moderna booster had been  about the same or better than to the primary vaccinations.   I actually double-checked with the pharmacist this morning that the booster dose is reduced to .25 ml, and they say that it is. I am writing about this adverse response because the booster shot is being so strongly advised, and required in some circumstances.    While I have been very pro-vaccine, I would be loath to have another booster if this is going to happen routinely - the reaction has been honestly frightening.  I wonder if there needs to be a closer look taken at the interval time and dose for this first booster.  While the first vaccinations were administered with lots of paperwork for reports of side effects, I received no such paperwork from the pharmacy.  I'm not at all comfortable that adverse reactions are being adequately monitored.

I noticed a slight ringing in both ears weeks after my first JJ shot. The shot made me terribly sick for a day and I felt awful for two days. Pounding headache, convulsing while curled into a ball with chills and sweats. I suspect neurological or nerve damage by whatever was going on. Booster shot (Moderna) made the ringing worse possibly doubled the noise just days later 1-3 days. Both ears now ring loud enough to hear while walking outside or in the office at work. I also hear a fluttering or pulsing sound almost like pressure or heartbeats, usually fast but sometimes pressure sounds from my actual heart beat which is not as bothersome as the ringing. A doctor prescribed me 250mg of oral steroid pills for 4 days which made my face and eyes puffy, vision really blurry and made it hard to sleep. The pills did nothing at all.  The doctor stated that I don't have any hearing loss and thought it might be stress But I have not been under any stress ever. So if the ringing is not stress related, nor caused by hearing loss and happened within 24-72 hours of the shot, I'm suspecting the shot caused the tinnitus.   Previously, I was not on medications and nearly never on medications my entire life.
LAB_DATA: No hearing loss. Normal readings.

Following the vaccine, I began having GI issues as well as hypertension. On May 15, 2021 the worst yet happened. I had severe abdominal pain radiating up my entire left chest. After the vaccine, I would randomly have this same type of abdominal pain that was relieved with time within a few hours it would go away naturally. But in May it did not go away for nearly two days, I went to an urgent care, family doctor, and the ER. I had multiple tests done, thousands in medical bills. Since May I have been to 5 different doctors, had multiple tests and procedures done with no answer as to why this is occurring to me intermittently. Throughout this entire process and the numbers of doctors I have seen, I have also developed high blood pressure. I never had this before the vaccine. I now have high blood pressure every time I see a doctor, they are unsure why and I have pending tests on my kidneys for this reason. I have absolutely no other medical history, I am normal weight, exercise daily and have no other medical issues or family history of. This all occurred after the vaccine and, as I am a registered nurse and cannot find any other reason for these issues,  I believe the vaccine caused these adverse effects.
LAB_DATA: May 15, 2021: limited abdominal ultrasound- negative; Pregnancy test- negative; Labs such as CBC, CMP, Lipase, UA- all negative.  5/24/2021: Ultrasound abdominal complete- all normal/negative. Pelvic ultrasound negative. 7/14/2021: Colonoscopy- no colitis, terminal ilium normal, otherwise inconclusive due to stool in colon.  12/22/2021: Upper GI X ray with marsh mellow bagel study: Negative  Pending EGD and renal ultrasound.  multiple follow ups and appointments during these past months since the vaccine.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 30 minutes after first dose I began getting pins and needles sensations in my arms and hands. 40 minutes after first dose I began feeling numbness in my face. These sensations came and went throughout the rest of the day. The facial numbness came and went throughout day two as well. Then 12 hours after the first dose, pain in the injection arm began to radiate throughout my arm down into my hand and then up into my neck and shoulders. I was not able to raise my arm on day two and had painful headaches and neck and back pain for the next 3 days. These effects seemed to resolve after about day three.   In Feb. I got the second dose -- no effects for the first two days and then about 50 to 60 hours after the second dose I began feeling very unwell and weird as if I had been poisoned. I began feeling fatigue, nausea, headaches, body aches, brain fog. These lasted for about 12 or 13 days. Around day 7 or so symptoms were getting worse with night sweats (no registered fever) and heart palpitations that came and went. The last night of symptoms I had a sudden onset of severe abdominal pain that lasted about 4 hours, from about 10pm to 2am or so. I would say it was a level 8 or 9 out of 10. I considered going to the ER but then the pain subsided after about 4 hours and on day 13 I seemed to be OK although  a year later I still get some headaches and heart racing and fluttering, a few times a week.
LAB_DATA: At the time I did not, and do not currently have, a primary care physician so I never saw a doctor about this. I am on two waitlists to see doctors about my headaches and heart racing.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Woke up around 3am with full body shakes as if from a seizure or extreme panic attack. lasted for several minutes. Experienced extreme anxiety and yelled for help. I immediately began rubbing magnesium body butter into his feet, which seemed to help the shaking subside. Military base was notified, but no evaluation or testing was done. They referred him to a single therapy session and told him he was "stressed" and needed to exercise and meditate more.  The following day, he several days, he had severe headache, elevated heart rate, palpitations, brain fog, felt feverish, but with no fever... around day 3 he had a couple nights of intense night sweats, and afterward his daytime symptoms improved, but he continued to come home from work complaining of dizzy spells, brain fog, and feeling like he may lose consciousness.   Ever since the initial episode on Nov 7th, he has continued to wake up in the night with varying degrees of anxiety- sometimes feeling like he may start shaking again, sometimes just needing to grab my hand for reassurance. This was not happening before Nov 7th.  Also, he and I are currently sick with Covid- same symptoms, same severity- even though he should still be "protected" as he had his vaccination less than 8 weeks ago. So, it did nothing to help him, just make him sick.
LAB_DATA: Base was notified of reactions, but it was written off as "normal" and no tests were ordered.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: The day of getting the vaccine I drove back to work and continued my work as normal at my desk , until I started to get numb and eventually my whole body was numb,weak and I was burning up with sweating palms and it Almost felt like an intoxicating very weak feeling and I was very out of it. For a couple hours  I was sitting at my  desk weak and couldn?t work. Everyone I talked to about it said it was normal so I just got a ride home and got some rest. The next day I went to work that morning cuz I was feeling better and around 8-830 my right arm where I got the vaccine starting goin numb then it started to turn white and felt like I was losing circulation I called the walk-in clinic and asked if that was normal and she said I should go to the emergency room as soon as possible. One of my supervisors told me should go to the office at my work and they ended up making the decision to call the ems and take to me the hospital. While waiting for the ems my hand started looking blue and splotchy. And I got so weak I could barley stay awake. Had to take some time off work and I?m rest up but Im still pretty weak. At the hospital they told me everything was normal and that was a possible reaction and sent me home within a short amount of time.

About a month after the 2nd dose, I started having a pain in my chest. The doctor thought it might be anxiety so it was treated as such but it kept getting worse. Around Thanksgiving I thought I was having an attack of some kind even though I?d never had heart problems in the past. I called the doctor and was scheduled immediately for a gallbladder ultrasound, EKG, and lab work. The EKG revealed a right bundle branch block that has a known cause of myocarditis. I am under the care of a cardiologist currently and have more tests scheduled this week.
LAB_DATA: EKG, lab work 11/30/21
HISTORY: Diagnosed with a Right Bundle Branch Block in December of 2021 and currently under the care of a cardiologist for ongoing heart related issues that did not occur until after the 2nd Covid shot (moderna).

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 11/19 Injection.  Swollen, painful bruised arm for days 11/21 (Sunday night) Not able to sleep. 11/22 (Monday): Still dark bruised arm. Bump under injection site. Stomach pain and unable to asleep 11/23 (Tuesday): Stomach pain during the night. Refused food in the morning. Bizarre behavior. Lasted a few days. 12/13 (Monday): Awake several hours during the night with a full itchy body that included little hives and bumps on torso and legs, and a lot of post nasal drip/throat clearing irritation. Itching lasted several days. 12/18 (Sunday): Stomach pain and not able to fall asleep. Woke up at 5, vomiting by 7am.  12/19 (Monday): Back to sleep around 9am. Up at 11, fever, stomach pain, back to sleep. Additional information for Item 18:  12/19 (Monday): Back to sleep around 9. Up at 11, fever, stomach pain, back to sleep. Woke up and unable to walk. Crying his body hurt so bad. Went to Children's UC, then referred to ER. They said "GI Virus" and dehydration. Fever. My son has never had pain like this before - ever. 12/20 � 24 (Tuesday � Friday) Heavy congestion. Fever again on Thursday night. 12/24 (Friday) 2pm Bloody noses. With big clots. Mild fever. Just an hour prior he went from a happy little boy for Christmas to absent minded, aloof, dead look in his yes, buried face from family, doubled over stomach pain. 5pm, more of the same + head pain 8/10 scale.  First responder friends provided initial direction of 30 minutes for headache to calm, then go to ER. Children's recommended ER.  We went to ER. Flu, CV, and RSV all negative.  At this point I am looking back at last month of health abnormalities and suspect what we have seen is covid 19 pediatric vaccine reactions.   For weeks my son has been complaining things taste or smell bad to the point he gags and refuses to eat or drink. Basic things like even filtered, tap, and well water.  Allopathic providers dismissed concerns of correlation to cv19 vaccine, all other medical folks and observers did not dismiss.  In 2018 I accepted my son was having reactions to previous 'normal' vaccines. His father did not accept and mandated through Judge my son continue 'normal' vaccination.  As a mother I did not approve of this non FDA approved shot; his father did this behind my back.
PRIOR_VAX: Several reactions from newborn to age 5 (Flu. Hep A, DTAP, MMR, Hep B)

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Six hours after receiving the vaccine, I developed severe full body tremors and facial twitching including eyes, rapid and irregular heartbeat, high blood pressure, fatigue, headache, weakness in my legs due to shaking from tremors. When I went to my doctors office two days later and he saw my condition he said I needed to see a neurologist for possible Parkinson?s disease or Lyme disease. The two neurologists I saw said they were both seeing many patients with this reaction to the vaccine.  I had an MRI of the brain to rule out Parkinsons disease. I was put on 60 mgs of Propanolol to help control the tremors but it didn?t completely work so dose was raised to 120 mgs. I saw the cardiologist who did an echo stress test on 08/16/2021 as the symptoms persisted, both tremors and heart. On May 11 2021 I wore a 30 day heart monitor which diagnosed an arrythmia. My blood pressure continues to be high. I had a nuclear medicine myocardial stress test on 09/08/2021 which was normal. I am currently on 40 mgs of propranolol to control the tremors. I have tremors nearly every day. I contacted Moderna on 03/03/2021. My case numbers are MOD21-043326 and subsequently contacted them with case numbers MOD21-121787, MOD21-121807. They have never called me back. I have been told by 3 doctors not to get another covid vaccine.

11 Y/O pt, was administered Pfizer pediatric first dose.  Pt consent form was reviewed and all question were answered no. Pt received the vaccine without problem and then sat down in front of the pharmacy to wait for 15 minutes. After approximately 5 minutes pt wasn't feeling well and started crying and father called me, and the Pharmacist, over to the patient. Tech and myself ran to the patient.  The patient was complaining of not feeling well and her eyes felt weird. Upon examining the patient I found her eyes, lips, and face beginning to swell. At this point I called for a tech to bring the Epi-pen, call code white and call 911.  I assessed the patient breathing, airways, and circulation and they were good. Due to the facial swelling and distress from the patient I administered a dose of Epi-pen Jr into the patients left thigh.  Within minutes after administering the dose the pt said she was feeling better.  She continued saying she was having waves of nausea, some dizziness and felt like she was "in a dream." She did vomit 2 times after the dose was administered before EMS arrived.  We monitored the patient while waiting for EMS and she continued to progress with feeling better.  Once EMS arrived, I spoke with them about the what happen and administering the Epi-Pen.  They checked the pt's vitals and they were all good.  The pt felt well enough at this point to walk with EMS to the ambulance.   Pt returned to pharmacy later that day and had fully recovered.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I had an allergic reaction to salmon 2 weeks following my vaccination.  After filling out my survey, I was asked to fill out this report.  My doctor indicates salmon as a common allergy and I am getting seen by an allergist hopefully in February.  I had never had a reaction to salmon prior to this event.  On both Friday the 3rd, and Saturday the 4th, my hands swelled up, I became very itchy all over, and showed signs of dermatographia.  I was provided a 5 day dose of prednisone which eliminated the itchiness and swelling, but dermatographia continued.  I was provided a second 5 day dose of prednisone, had a blood test, and have since been fine, but have been avoiding all seafood until I get an allergy test.
LAB_DATA: I had a follow up doctor appointment with blood test on December 23rd.  Nothing was identified of concern.  (per nurse)  Follow on allergy testing is expected.
OTHER_MEDS: Simvastatin 40mg (daily) Loratadine (daily) Vitamin D 5000IU (daily) Vitamin B (every other day)
ALLERGIES: Hydrocodone Salmon (new development on the 3rd - and why I was asked to submit this)

The adverse events being reported and documented below are death from unexplained spontaneous bleeding (thinning of the blood) that followed acute inflammation and excruciating pain that began less than 48 hours after the second dose of the Moderna vaccine.Timeline of events from March 4 - May 2, 2021; 3/4/21  - Second dose of Moderna Covid-19 vaccine received. 3/5/21  - Mom) reported being very tired and nauseous. 3/6/21  - (Mom) reported being in extreme pain which turned into excruciating pain. Timeline of events from March 4 - May 2, 2021  Note:  (Mom) had a very high tolerance for pain, evidenced by previous major falls & fractured bones (pelvis, hip, both femurs, 9 ribs, 3 cracked vertebrae), the lingering results of which she lived with every day without constant mention of the chronic pain.  In contrast, the pain that began on March 6 was excruciating, incapacitating, and resulted in her barely being able to walk and was, therefore, new, noteworthy, different and unusual.  3/08/21 - Visit #1 to the ER  for excruciating pain. - Pelvic x-ray done, nothing broken; IV morphine given. - Examination by ER physician. - Released from hospital; sent home with script for Norco for pain; did not take because it made her unable to function.  Note:   (Mom) identified the source of her excruciating pain to the ER physician as being in her lower left back region, just at the top of her left pelvic bone, as witnessed by a family member.   3/22/21 - Visit #2 to the ER  Hospital for same excruciating pain (as March 8) and ultimately admitted. - EKG, CT scan, MRI spine, MRI pelvis and whole-body bone scan done during length of stay.  No new findings, only evidence of old fractures and spondylolisthesis, all of which were known, old diagnoses.  3/23/21 - Examination by PA-C for Chief of Orthopedics and subsequently by Hospital.  Note:  Despite the fact that this was the second admission in three weeks for the same pain that was originating from the same source, the orthopedic specialists focused on old compression fractures, old pelvic fractures, and degenerative spinal changes, which (Mom) lived with every day with little complaint.  The source of the excruciating pain that began on March 6, and that was reported on March 8 in the ER, appeared to have been excluded from consideration or discussion.  3/26/21 - Released from hospital with short course of steroids for pain; minute reduction in pain until steroid dose was weaned and the same excruciating pain, that began on March 6, immediately emerged again.  4/7/21   - Visit #3 to the ER  for same excruciating pain (as March 8) and ultimately admitted. - Lumbar/AP spine and dorsal/thoracic spine x-rays, front pelvic & 2 view left hip x-rays, front chest & 3 bilateral rib x-rays, EKG, Echo done during length of stay. - Examination by Hospitalist Internal Medicine.   - Examination by Orthopedic Surgeon.   - Examination by Pain Management Specialist/Neurologist.  4/10/21 - (Mom's) acute inflammation and excruciating pain were diagnosed as Trochanteric Bursitis.  A Depo-Medrol steroid shot was given in left hip area by Pain Management Specialist/Neurologist for the acute inflammation and pain (Mom) had been experiencing for the five weeks since the second Covid-19 shot; pain relief within hours after the steroid shot.  By the end of the day, she went from not being able to walk to walking to the end of the hallway within the hospital.   4/13/21 -  (Mom) was to be transferred Hospital  for rehab program, however, due to spontaneous bleeding of her fistula, she was kept at Hospital for observation.  (Mom's) Vascular Surgeon was called in to help stop the bleeding.    Note:  The spontaneous bleeding from (Mom's) fistula seemed highly unusual as it had never occurred in six years of receiving dialysis.    4/15/21 - Fistulogram performed by Vascular & Interventional Radiology Specialist to ensure fistula was in good working order.  Results showed no stenosis.                  4/16/21 - Transferred to Hospital  for inpatient physical therapy rehab program.  4/23/21 - Released from hospital after successful completion of the rehab program. (Mom) had a positive frame of mind and was looking forward to future plans.  She was able to walk again with the aid of her walker and to function independently; in-home therapy began 4/29 to build up strength she had lost during the 5 weeks of excruciating pain and time spent in the hospital.  5/2/21 -  Spontaneous bleeding from fistula, no blood pressure, heart stopped.  Cause of death ruled (spontaneous) bleeding from fistula.
LAB_DATA: See Continuation Page for timeline of events, lab results, treatment and outcomes.
OTHER_MEDS: Norvasc, Aspirin, Coreg, Phoslo, Dialyvite, Synthroid, Vit D3, Probiotic, Turmeric, Omega 3 fish oil, Vit B Complex
HISTORY: High blood pressure (controlled), CHF (controlled), ESRD (In-Center Hemodialysis)

She had a stroke on April 1st, 2021 while at the Nurse's office, according to my mom & symptoms. She died on April 23rd as a result. Facility does not have a lot of equipment. She had tests done at another facility.   Mom had a stroke on April 1st, 2021. My sister and I recognized it as a stroke on the phone, just talking to my mom. The nurses & medical personnel at the facility did not acknowledge or seem to recognize that she had had a stroke. It took them all the next day to get her transported to the Hospital. The Hospital did say she had a stroke (see 1st page of medical report). We believe the vaccine & shot stroke may be related. The Facility may be trying to cover up something (esp. the stroke).  All day at Nurses office was admitted to hospital at facility later in the day.  They dragged her around all day until she had a stroke while there. Did not transport her until late on April 2nd.  Discharge Diagnosis:  Stroke Acute GI Bleeding Acute diastolic heart failure Aortic stenosis Arthritis, on chronic prednisone HTN DM2 Hyperlipidemia, unspecified Urinary tract infection  Surgical Procedures: ESOPHAGOGASTRODUODENOSCOPY EGD W/ peg tube 04/14/2021 14:21 placement  Hospital Course: Patient is an 83-year-old female with past medical history of prior ischemic stroke and cerebral aneurysm w/p coiling, as well as HTN and DM2, who presented from an outside facility due to new stroke.  The patient began feeling poorly several days prior to her admission to the outside hospital.  She became increasingly short of breath and developed lower extremity swelling.  She was evaluated in the ED and found to have an elevated BNP of 1700.  She was admitted and started on scheduled IV Lasix diuresis.  Around 8:45 PM the evening of transfer to our facility, the patient developed new slurred speech, difficulty swallowing, and left facial droop.  A CT of the head was done, and showed evidence of old stroke and prior aneurysm coiling but no acute abnormality. The case was discussed with MD of neurology and the patient was transferred to another facility for a higher level of care.  On arrival here, an MRI of the brain was done, and showed right frontal and left cerebellar infarcts.  MRA of the head was unremarkable.  2D echocardiogram showed a preserved LVEF of 75-80% without evidence of PFO of clot.  Carotid Doppler showed no significant stenosis.  The patient was evaluated by speech therapy, who recommended strict n.p.o. status due to her high risk of aspiration.  She ultimately required placement of a PEG tube on 04/14/2021.  Her ischemic stroke was otherwise managed with Plavix and a statin.
LAB_DATA: Current hospital does not have a lot of equipment. She had tests done at different site.
OTHER_MEDS: I do not have a list of all the medications with me. I am her oldest daughter. My other sister has a list. I know she was on high blood pressure meds, and predisone.
CUR_ILL: She had taken some shots for her back pain. She was considered a diabetic, but controlled with diet (not on insulin).
HISTORY: She had a stroke one week after taking the vaccine. On April 1, 2021 she was slurring her words on the phone. We asked nurse to check on her. Sounded like she had a stroke. Nurse said she was just tired. However, she had had a stroke. Jaw was also drooping and trouble swallowing.
ALLERGIES: Allergic to iodine, penicillian and codene, sulfa, shrimp
